page.title: 15BIRD LIFE OF THE AREA
page.content: {Local residents}of the area include blackbirds,blue tits,chaffinches, coal-tits,crows,great-tits,greenfinch es,house-sparrows,jackdaws,kestrels, magpies,owls,pigeons,robins,rooks, skylarks,sparrow-hawks,starlings, thrushes,wrens,wagtails and yellow hammers. {Migratory visitors }include swallows and house martins.Cuckoos return each spring to lay in the nests of the birds nesting on the burrows,on the sides of disused clay pits and in the marshy surroundings of the old pits now filled with pale blue water. Canadian Geese flying to and from the Arctic Circle, spend a night on the pond at Mr and Mrs Earl's small holding on Trerank Moor.
